WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.548 --> 00:00:08.634
-This the place?
-This the place.

2
00:00:12.846 --> 00:00:14.348
-This the stuff?
-This the stuff.

3
00:00:14.431 --> 00:00:16.183
And this is no ordinary stuff.
Morty.

4
00:00:16.265 --> 00:00:18.727
This sap is primo.

5
00:00:24.691 --> 00:00:25.984
-Argh!
-Ah!

6
00:00:26.026 --> 00:00:27.986
-What the hell?
-Shit! Vines!

7
00:00:29.363 --> 00:00:33.075
Locusts come
to harvest my bounty.

8
00:00:33.158 --> 00:00:34.785
Hey. giant ancient tree guy.

9
00:00:34.826 --> 00:00:37.329
Sorry. We thought
the sap was accountability free.

10
00:00:37.412 --> 00:00:40.541
Yeah. well. we're not locusts.
just a couple adventurers.

11
00:00:40.624 --> 00:00:42.834
Spacefarers.

12
00:00:42.876 --> 00:00:44.795
You consume your planets.

13
00:00:44.836 --> 00:00:48.590
then spread your sickness
to the stars.

14
00:00:48.674 --> 00:00:50.968
Nah. Nah. man.
We're clean. I promise.

15
00:00:51.009 --> 00:00:52.237
Yeah. yeah. We just got tested.

16
00:00:52.261 --> 00:00:54.137
and I got a bit of
a soy allergy.

17
00:00:54.179 --> 00:00:57.975
I have a place
for animals like you.

18
00:00:58.016 --> 00:01:01.728
You will be reformed.

19
00:01:04.730 --> 00:01:06.567
What is...

20
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:14.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

21
00:01:23.625 --> 00:01:25.043
This?!

22
00:01:25.127 --> 00:01:26.169
Yeah. Morty.

23
00:01:26.211 --> 00:01:27.713
Not ideal.

24
00:01:27.754 --> 00:01:29.590
But I promise you.
the sap will be worth it.

25
00:01:29.673 --> 00:01:32.467
I had the craziest night
on this stuff a few weeks ago.

26
00:02:04.249 --> 00:02:05.792
I'm all wobbly. Rick.

27
00:02:05.876 --> 00:02:06.918
What the fuck's going on.

28
00:02:07.002 --> 00:02:08.919
In the same position you are.

29
00:02:09.003 --> 00:02:10.898
But I can guess that those roots
extracted the biological data

30
00:02:10.922 --> 00:02:13.592
we think of as our minds
and reincarnated us as amoeba.

31
00:02:13.675 --> 00:02:15.594
How do we get our
old bodies back?

32
00:02:15.636 --> 00:02:17.471
Well. that's the wrong question.

33
00:02:17.554 --> 00:02:19.431
But it's the one all
new cellmates ask.

34
00:02:19.514 --> 00:02:21.433
"Cellmates."

35
00:02:21.516 --> 00:02:23.685
We use humor to stay sane
in this place.

36
00:02:23.769 --> 00:02:24.936
Yes. sir.

37
00:02:25.020 --> 00:02:26.372
Many folks have tried
to raid this planet

38
00:02:26.396 --> 00:02:27.773
and ended up down here.

39
00:02:27.856 --> 00:02:29.191
Growth and rebirth.

40
00:02:29.232 --> 00:02:30.418
The ball and chain
around our ankles.

41
00:02:30.442 --> 00:02:32.653
In here. a man can truly change.

42
00:02:32.736 --> 00:02:34.905
But don't mistake that
for freedom.

43
00:02:34.946 --> 00:02:37.156
Give me your cytoplasm.
you limp-dick motherfucker!

44
00:02:39.493 --> 00:02:40.577
Argh!

45
00:02:46.917 --> 00:02:48.126
What? Huh.

46
00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:49.461
Guess if you die.
you start over.

47
00:02:49.543 --> 00:02:51.129
Good thing
we hadn't made much progress.

48
00:02:51.171 --> 00:02:52.464
Try not to die. Morty.

49
00:02:52.506 --> 00:02:53.799
Hello. my delicious friends.

50
00:02:53.882 --> 00:02:54.966
He's multicellular now!

51
00:02:55.050 --> 00:02:56.301
Back for another helping?

52
00:02:56.385 --> 00:02:57.594
Spawn-camping piece of shit!

53
00:02:57.636 --> 00:02:59.346
Jesus!

54
00:02:59.429 --> 00:03:01.240
Prison rules. Morty.
Get to the top of the food chain

55
00:03:01.264 --> 00:03:02.349
or you're someone's dinner.

56
00:03:03.850 --> 00:03:05.477
Hey. get in here.
We need the nutrients.

57
00:03:06.395 --> 00:03:08.563
Oh. it's like salty tapioca.

58
00:03:08.647 --> 00:03:10.792
If this place is dumb enough
to let us manipulate our DNA.

59
00:03:10.816 --> 00:03:12.734
Morty. then we'll
just evolve our way out.

60
00:03:12.776 --> 00:03:13.902
First step is fins.

61
00:03:13.944 --> 00:03:15.987
Wait. How? Mitosis. Morty.

62
00:03:16.029 --> 00:03:18.156
Think really hard
about being your own daughter.

63
00:03:26.415 --> 00:03:27.791
Being a fish isn't so bad.

64
00:03:27.833 --> 00:03:29.543
Swimming is fun.

65
00:03:29.626 --> 00:03:31.169
I do like
how you're never thirsty.

66
00:03:31.211 --> 00:03:32.963
And the whole world's
your toilet.

67
00:03:39.136 --> 00:03:40.512
Oh. Oh. air.

68
00:03:40.554 --> 00:03:41.346
So good.

69
00:03:41.430 --> 00:03:42.889
So good.

70
00:03:52.816 --> 00:03:54.025
Toughen up. Morty.

71
00:03:54.109 --> 00:03:55.670
The primordial soup was
just the beginning.

72
00:03:55.694 --> 00:03:57.195
We're in some kind of
hollow earth.

73
00:03:57.279 --> 00:03:59.322
The reincarnation field
must be contained

74
00:03:59.364 --> 00:04:00.633
within the warden's
root lattice.

75
00:04:00.657 --> 00:04:01.950
If we escape to the surface.

76
00:04:02.033 --> 00:04:03.034
we escape the cycle.

77
00:04:05.579 --> 00:04:08.039
God damn it. Morty.
you're a lungfish.

78
00:04:08.081 --> 00:04:10.917
Use your lungs.

79
00:04:26.183 --> 00:04:27.684
Sorry.

80
00:04:27.726 --> 00:04:29.203
You know how much willpower
it takes to drown yourself?

81
00:04:29.227 --> 00:04:30.455
W-What do you want to try next?

82
00:04:30.479 --> 00:04:32.731
I got eight words for you...

83
00:04:32.773 --> 00:04:34.733
legs.

84
00:04:34.775 --> 00:04:36.067
This is great.

85
00:04:36.109 --> 00:04:37.837
We let our food come to us
and plan our next move.

86
00:04:37.861 --> 00:04:39.404
Um. I think I'm stuck.

87
00:04:39.488 --> 00:04:40.822
In our own web?

88
00:04:40.906 --> 00:04:42.991
It's fine.
I'll use you and pull myself up.

89
00:04:43.074 --> 00:04:44.075
Don't!

90
00:04:44.159 --> 00:04:45.577
Oh! Damn it!

91
00:04:45.619 --> 00:04:48.455
Not so fun. is it?

92
00:04:48.538 --> 00:04:50.415
Eat shit! I'm gonna!

93
00:04:50.457 --> 00:04:52.334
Morty. I'm gonna evolve wings.

94
00:04:52.417 --> 00:04:53.960
and then I'm gonna
kill that guy.

95
00:04:55.545 --> 00:04:57.130
Whoo-hoo!

96
00:04:57.214 --> 00:04:58.673
This is amazing. Rick.

97
00:04:58.757 --> 00:05:00.258
And really quick to get to.

98
00:05:00.300 --> 00:05:02.177
Birds are basically
small dinosaurs.

99
00:05:02.761 --> 00:05:04.721
All right. Morty.
there's no thermals.

100
00:05:04.763 --> 00:05:07.265
So we've got to evolve really
specific wings to get up there.

101
00:05:07.307 --> 00:05:08.934
Oh. you can't build us
mech suits yet.

102
00:05:08.975 --> 00:05:10.685
Nah. birds can get
wherever they want.

103
00:05:10.727 --> 00:05:12.479
but can't do anything
once they get there.

104
00:05:12.562 --> 00:05:14.105
It's like astral projection.

105
00:05:14.189 --> 00:05:15.315
Oh. shit!

106
00:05:15.398 --> 00:05:16.817
He can get us down here. too.

107
00:05:22.781 --> 00:05:24.741
All right. Pretty obvious.

108
00:05:24.783 --> 00:05:26.260
We gotta climb a tech tree
to climb the actual tree.

109
00:05:26.284 --> 00:05:28.495
And we do that with...

110
00:05:28.578 --> 00:05:31.456
Hands. Supple. grippy hands

111
00:05:31.540 --> 00:05:33.291
and a pretty familiar version
of...

112
00:05:33.332 --> 00:05:36.127
God. just go already.
Don't wait up!

113
00:05:41.091 --> 00:05:44.261
Um. this watering hole is
pretty tense.

114
00:05:44.302 --> 00:05:47.472
Pretty. um. ape heavy. Exactly.

115
00:05:47.556 --> 00:05:50.725
There's holes for apes only.
Clear out.

116
00:05:50.767 --> 00:05:53.311
Oh. we were just.
uh. drinking water.

117
00:05:53.395 --> 00:05:54.771
And using tools!

118
00:05:54.813 --> 00:05:57.482
Hey. look.
this guy's jerking off a stick

119
00:05:57.524 --> 00:05:58.567
with his rock.

120
00:05:58.650 --> 00:06:00.193
He's a stick stroker!

121
00:06:00.277 --> 00:06:01.945
I'm gonna end you. tool man.

122
00:06:01.987 --> 00:06:04.155
We. uh. we-we-we
we can move along.

123
00:06:04.197 --> 00:06:05.365
Argh!

124
00:06:06.992 --> 00:06:08.326
Oh. my God. Rick!

125
00:06:08.368 --> 00:06:09.512
Hey. what the fuck?
Hey! Kill those monkeys

126
00:06:09.536 --> 00:06:10.616
slightly different than us.

127
00:06:10.662 --> 00:06:12.247
What are you doing. Rick?

128
00:06:12.330 --> 00:06:14.875
They started it. Domination
through technology. Morty.

129
00:06:14.958 --> 00:06:17.961
We're going apex.
This stick is your god!

130
00:06:18.003 --> 00:06:19.004
He's got a thing!

131
00:06:20.338 --> 00:06:21.298
Oh!

132
00:06:21.339 --> 00:06:22.507
Ri... Rick?

133
00:06:22.632 --> 00:06:23.818
I'm doing this for both of us.

134
00:06:23.842 --> 00:06:25.802
I'll find you when I find you.

135
00:06:29.681 --> 00:06:31.433
Guess he really did bail on me.

136
00:06:31.516 --> 00:06:32.517
You lost. son?

137
00:06:32.558 --> 00:06:34.352
Oh. Oh. hey. Uh. please...

138
00:06:34.436 --> 00:06:36.146
Please don't kill me
for my cytoplasm.

139
00:06:36.187 --> 00:06:37.689
Oh. child.

140
00:06:37.731 --> 00:06:40.442
you've been trapped in
the cycle of violence too long.

141
00:06:40.483 --> 00:06:42.485
I don't know.
maybe you're right.

142
00:06:42.527 --> 00:06:44.279
I'm tired of fighting
all the time.

143
00:06:44.362 --> 00:06:45.947
Mm-hmm.

144
00:06:45.989 --> 00:06:48.533
I've seen countless souls
waste a billion lifetimes trying

145
00:06:48.575 --> 00:06:49.951
to bust out of here.

146
00:06:50.034 --> 00:06:51.745
But you can't fight
the cycle. son.

147
00:06:51.828 --> 00:06:54.456
You got to submit to it.
Serve nature.

148
00:06:54.539 --> 00:06:56.957
Is this where you kill me?

149
00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:59.336
Oh. you are traumatized.

150
00:07:05.467 --> 00:07:06.885
Wow!

151
00:07:06.968 --> 00:07:08.571
Pollinating. building
little hexagon houses.

152
00:07:08.595 --> 00:07:10.305
feels good to do
something positive.

153
00:07:10.388 --> 00:07:11.306
Mm-hmm.

154
00:07:11.389 --> 00:07:12.724
You see?

155
00:07:12.766 --> 00:07:13.868
And I reckon the warden
likes it. too.

156
00:07:13.892 --> 00:07:15.852
What are you in for. Morty?

157
00:07:15.894 --> 00:07:18.897
I was a scout for an orc species
looking for planets to conquer.

158
00:07:18.939 --> 00:07:21.066
I was a scout
for a sludge species looking

159
00:07:21.149 --> 00:07:22.525
for planets to conquer.

160
00:07:22.567 --> 00:07:24.694
Well. I'm a touch different

161
00:07:24.736 --> 00:07:28.907
because I was a pod person
looking for planets to conquer.

162
00:07:28.949 --> 00:07:31.159
I was helping
my grandpa get sap.

163
00:07:31.242 --> 00:07:33.370
I assume it makes energy
or gets you high.

164
00:07:33.411 --> 00:07:34.663
I-I-I don't know.

165
00:07:34.746 --> 00:07:36.748
Aha. That adds up.

166
00:07:36.831 --> 00:07:39.918
He seems the type to be
locked in here. but you don't.

167
00:07:39.960 --> 00:07:41.002
Thank you!

168
00:07:41.086 --> 00:07:43.421
It's a... There's a...

169
00:07:43.463 --> 00:07:46.216
G-O-R...

170
00:07:47.008 --> 00:07:51.221
Should've... spelled... "ape."

171
00:07:52.681 --> 00:07:54.057
On to the next one.

172
00:07:54.099 --> 00:07:56.433
Every cycle evolves
as closer to parole.

173
00:07:58.937 --> 00:08:02.774
Ohhhh. I'm so fucking wounded.

174
00:08:02.816 --> 00:08:03.960
Everyone follow my lead. Owwww.

175
00:08:03.984 --> 00:08:05.652
Your lead? I'm the alpha.

176
00:08:05.735 --> 00:08:06.945
Dog. I'm the alpha.

177
00:08:07.028 --> 00:08:10.198
Easy prey here. Easy pickings.

178
00:08:10.281 --> 00:08:11.241
Get em. Now!

179
00:08:11.282 --> 00:08:13.827
I'm the alpha. Omega!

180
00:08:13.910 --> 00:08:16.079
A hole? This isn't alpha at all.

181
00:08:16.121 --> 00:08:19.624
We're all betas now.
Come on. time to meet the boss.

182
00:08:23.086 --> 00:08:26.256
Hey. I know usually I'd
be trying to eat you and all.

183
00:08:26.297 --> 00:08:27.799
but maybe Los Lobos in the herd.

184
00:08:27.882 --> 00:08:30.301
Hey! No interspecies solidarity.

185
00:08:35.765 --> 00:08:37.642
The wolves have
been incorporated. sir.

186
00:08:37.726 --> 00:08:39.852
All except for that one.

187
00:08:39.936 --> 00:08:42.313
I'm sorry for those things
I said about apes.

188
00:08:42.397 --> 00:08:44.190
More fermented berry mash.

189
00:08:44.274 --> 00:08:47.152
Right away. sir.
It's time to climb this fucker.

190
00:08:52.532 --> 00:08:53.992
Listen up. pawns.

191
00:08:54.034 --> 00:08:56.077
We begin the task
of scaling this root.

192
00:08:56.161 --> 00:08:58.997
The root will kill you
if you touch it.

193
00:08:59.039 --> 00:09:01.833
You will go one at a time
for observation purposes.

194
00:09:01.916 --> 00:09:03.293
On. now.

195
00:09:03.334 --> 00:09:05.712
Kind of feel like I'm
being punished for my loyalty.

196
00:09:05.795 --> 00:09:07.505
Lead by example. Gorilla #3.

197
00:09:23.188 --> 00:09:24.481
Gas 20 feet up.

198
00:09:24.522 --> 00:09:26.024
Next!

199
00:09:37.535 --> 00:09:38.828
You know what? Fine.

200
00:09:38.870 --> 00:09:41.206
If we can't break out.
we break him.

201
00:09:58.640 --> 00:09:59.641
Ugh!

202
00:10:18.451 --> 00:10:20.912
So we clean shit from the ocean?

203
00:10:20.954 --> 00:10:22.747
Ocean needs cleanin'.

204
00:10:24.415 --> 00:10:26.543
And we shit in the ocean?

205
00:10:26.584 --> 00:10:28.169
Ocean needs shittin'.

206
00:10:32.006 --> 00:10:35.760
And we shit in the soil while
eating shit out of the soil?

207
00:10:35.844 --> 00:10:38.304
You're pretty hung up on
the shit part of it. aren't you?

208
00:10:43.268 --> 00:10:44.936
What's troubling you. son?

209
00:10:44.978 --> 00:10:47.647
I mean. I like the
nonviolence. don't get me wrong.

210
00:10:47.730 --> 00:10:49.691
And having a shell is fun.

211
00:10:49.732 --> 00:10:52.026
but it just feels
like we're going in circles.

212
00:10:52.068 --> 00:10:54.612
Well. that's what
a healthy ecosystem is.

213
00:10:54.654 --> 00:10:56.364
Eventually. the warden
will notice

214
00:10:56.447 --> 00:10:57.991
our piety and set us free.

215
00:10:58.074 --> 00:11:00.827
Until then.
we find peace in here.

216
00:11:00.910 --> 00:11:03.621
So a reformed prisoner
is someone

217
00:11:03.705 --> 00:11:05.415
who doesn't want to leave
the prison?

218
00:11:05.456 --> 00:11:07.125
See? You get it.

219
00:11:07.167 --> 00:11:10.170
Oh. now you're probably
just hungry. Here.

220
00:11:10.253 --> 00:11:12.088
I guess I don't want to eat.
whoever that is.

221
00:11:12.130 --> 00:11:14.632
Now. son. that's a vegetable.

222
00:11:14.716 --> 00:11:16.843
No one picks being a vegetable.

223
00:11:16.926 --> 00:11:20.096
you'd have to really give up
to be one of those.

224
00:11:20.930 --> 00:11:23.808
Hey. uh. I think
I'm maybe gonna brave the rest

225
00:11:23.850 --> 00:11:25.810
of this life alone.

226
00:11:25.894 --> 00:11:27.604
Well. you know where to find us.

227
00:11:27.645 --> 00:11:29.147
We'll be eating shit.

228
00:11:47.123 --> 00:11:48.165
Hmm.

229
00:11:53.463 --> 00:11:54.463
Oh.

230
00:13:12.083 --> 00:13:15.295
Sun! Real sun!

231
00:13:17.130 --> 00:13:20.091
Oh. great Warden! I did it!
I figured it out!

232
00:13:20.174 --> 00:13:22.927
The goal is to be a plant.
like you!

233
00:13:23.011 --> 00:13:24.804
Oh... Whoa.

234
00:13:24.887 --> 00:13:26.848
So many nutrients in the soil
up here.

235
00:13:26.931 --> 00:13:28.391
Y-Yes.

236
00:13:28.433 --> 00:13:32.729
The life cycles of
the guilty provide nourishment.

237
00:13:32.770 --> 00:13:34.063
Oh.

238
00:13:34.105 --> 00:13:35.732
But that's more of a byproduct

239
00:13:35.773 --> 00:13:37.734
than the point of all this.
right?

240
00:13:40.778 --> 00:13:44.157
So I-I live up here now?

241
00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:47.452
Oh. uh. this is my spot.

242
00:13:47.535 --> 00:13:50.872
Okay. I-I ca... I can go
find my own planet.

243
00:13:50.955 --> 00:13:52.999
Ahhh.

244
00:13:53.082 --> 00:13:56.544
You would kinda need to be
a spacefarer for that.

245
00:13:56.627 --> 00:13:58.129
And I don't like those.

246
00:13:58.171 --> 00:14:00.923
But now you know
how cool it is to be a tree.

247
00:14:00.965 --> 00:14:02.925
Oh. Boink!

248
00:14:17.398 --> 00:14:20.109
Okay. we have that
bronze post-mortem in 10.

249
00:14:20.151 --> 00:14:23.321
followed by the all hands
on opposable thumbs.

250
00:14:29.494 --> 00:14:30.995
I'll reschedule.

251
00:14:32.914 --> 00:14:34.040
Look who it is.

252
00:14:34.123 --> 00:14:35.665
You don't have to do this. man.

253
00:14:35.750 --> 00:14:37.811
The system's rigged. H-He
wants us fighting each other.

254
00:14:37.835 --> 00:14:40.797
Sounds like I'm on the
right side of history. Morty!

255
00:14:42.340 --> 00:14:43.800
Alright. Morty.
let's shake a leg.

256
00:14:43.841 --> 00:14:45.176
When he respawns in a second.

257
00:14:45.218 --> 00:14:46.677
he's not gonna be
any less annoying.

258
00:14:46.719 --> 00:14:48.096
Rick?! Is this a coincidence?

259
00:14:48.179 --> 00:14:49.806
Y-You died
at the same time as me?

260
00:14:49.847 --> 00:14:51.516
I saw everything. buddy.

261
00:14:51.557 --> 00:14:52.993
You beat the system.
then the system beat back.

262
00:14:53.017 --> 00:14:54.811
Ugh! He's... He's evil. Rick!

263
00:14:54.852 --> 00:14:56.646
He's feeding off the cycle
of death!

264
00:14:56.687 --> 00:14:58.731
W-We're all just mulch!

265
00:14:58.815 --> 00:15:00.858
Damn. Pretty diabolical tree.

266
00:15:00.942 --> 00:15:03.403
I don't wanna be mulch!
I wanna go home!

267
00:15:03.486 --> 00:15:04.838
We have to stop killing
each other!

268
00:15:04.862 --> 00:15:06.447
We will. buddy.

269
00:15:06.531 --> 00:15:08.331
No more death now.
That's what feeds the tree.

270
00:15:08.366 --> 00:15:10.785
I'm back!

271
00:15:10.868 --> 00:15:13.704
After that. Now let's go.

272
00:15:14.288 --> 00:15:18.459
NAAAAAAAAAAAANTS
ingonyamaaaaa bag it hi baba...

273
00:15:20.253 --> 00:15:21.921
Thanks for indulging me.

274
00:15:22.004 --> 00:15:24.924
I'm not in the form of a lion.
but I did want to sing the song.

275
00:15:25.007 --> 00:15:26.884
Hello. inmates.

276
00:15:26.926 --> 00:15:28.886
Okay. I deserve that.

277
00:15:28.928 --> 00:15:30.346
But I have something to say.

278
00:15:30.388 --> 00:15:32.557
You expect us to listen to you?!

279
00:15:32.640 --> 00:15:36.644
No. I expect you
to listen to Morty.

280
00:15:36.686 --> 00:15:39.897
The Warden seems wise and stoic.
but he's just a big tree.

281
00:15:39.981 --> 00:15:41.858
Which means we can starve him
out!

282
00:15:41.899 --> 00:15:44.193
It's a hunger strike!
But for him.

283
00:15:44.235 --> 00:15:47.572
We'll all live peacefully
in a contained system.

284
00:15:47.655 --> 00:15:49.907
So instead of escaping.

285
00:15:49.991 --> 00:15:52.577
we'll live in a smaller.
shittier prison?

286
00:15:52.618 --> 00:15:53.578
I didn't say shittier!

287
00:15:53.619 --> 00:15:55.079
Gorilla 3. is that you?

288
00:15:55.121 --> 00:15:57.832
It's Hyena 3 now.
I got a new job.

289
00:15:57.915 --> 00:15:59.250
Seems like a lateral step.

290
00:15:59.292 --> 00:16:01.377
Th-Think of it more
as a bio do me.

291
00:16:01.419 --> 00:16:04.088
You've spent a million
lifetimes being dogs and fish.

292
00:16:04.172 --> 00:16:06.883
It won't kill you
to spend one lifetime on this.

293
00:16:06.924 --> 00:16:10.595
Hopefully nothing will kill you.
That's the point of the strike.

294
00:16:18.227 --> 00:16:21.772
Oh. this was a mistake.
What? This looks great!

295
00:16:21.856 --> 00:16:24.442
Then again. I am a bat.

296
00:16:24.525 --> 00:16:26.277
Welcome to ME!

297
00:16:26.319 --> 00:16:27.945
Combined with Morty's
plant-based livin'.

298
00:16:27.987 --> 00:16:29.947
we should all age
pretty gracefully.

299
00:16:29.989 --> 00:16:31.866
All he needs from you is...

300
00:16:31.949 --> 00:16:33.451
Hey. Mornin'.

301
00:16:33.493 --> 00:16:35.953
Shittin' hard or hardly
shittin'?

302
00:16:36.037 --> 00:16:38.206
Ya know. when they pitched me
on this herbivore diet.

303
00:16:38.289 --> 00:16:40.790
I was skeptical.
but then I tried the pizza.

304
00:17:12.156 --> 00:17:13.824
I need 34 bruschettas. all day.

305
00:17:13.866 --> 00:17:15.284
Yes. Chimp!

306
00:17:16.327 --> 00:17:18.119
And you laugh at all my jokes.

307
00:17:18.162 --> 00:17:21.415
It's true. it's true.

308
00:17:21.499 --> 00:17:23.419
I led us all down here
with the expressed purpose

309
00:17:23.459 --> 00:17:25.419
of killing our tree
warden overlord.

310
00:17:25.502 --> 00:17:27.630
which I remind you is
still our goal.

311
00:17:27.672 --> 00:17:29.423
He should actually be
pretty weak by now.

312
00:17:29.507 --> 00:17:32.343
However. I knew we were putting
down roots.

313
00:17:32.426 --> 00:17:34.345
but never imagined
love would bloom.

314
00:17:34.428 --> 00:17:36.472
What doesn't bloom down here?

315
00:17:37.932 --> 00:17:40.518
Ha ha ha. congratulations!

316
00:17:40.560 --> 00:17:43.020
Hyena 3 and Sheep.
you may now...

317
00:17:43.104 --> 00:17:45.815
Okay. already doing it. Hot.

318
00:17:48.192 --> 00:17:50.528
Ho-ho. let's par-tay!

319
00:17:57.618 --> 00:17:59.036
Ohhh.

320
00:17:59.120 --> 00:18:02.873
I'm so... hungry.

321
00:18:02.915 --> 00:18:06.627
Wh-What's happening down there?

322
00:18:08.504 --> 00:18:12.258
Hey! Start killing each other!

323
00:18:12.341 --> 00:18:16.554
Hello? Anybody?

324
00:18:16.637 --> 00:18:20.391
Oh. you little fuckers
are gonna get it now!

325
00:18:31.277 --> 00:18:33.696
"Get bent."

326
00:18:33.738 --> 00:18:36.824
Get bent? Little toothless.

327
00:18:36.907 --> 00:18:38.075
Not that I can beat it.

328
00:18:38.117 --> 00:18:39.493
Now!

329
00:18:40.786 --> 00:18:42.038
Aaaaah!

330
00:18:48.836 --> 00:18:51.213
It's working. He's too weak
to get us with his vines!

331
00:18:51.255 --> 00:18:53.716
Good thing. too.
I didn't anticipate how old

332
00:18:53.758 --> 00:18:56.427
and pacified our forces would be
by the time this plan worked.

333
00:18:56.469 --> 00:18:58.721
Come on. Hyena 3.
marriage made ya soft.

334
00:18:58.763 --> 00:19:01.724
Leave him alone!
You were always a toxic boss!

335
00:19:04.393 --> 00:19:06.896
It's working! Phase 2 now!

336
00:19:19.283 --> 00:19:20.326
Pull!

337
00:19:23.788 --> 00:19:24.955
No!

338
00:19:24.997 --> 00:19:28.334
This planet was my retirement!

339
00:19:28.417 --> 00:19:30.044
Say it with me. animals!

340
00:19:30.127 --> 00:19:32.546
Timber!

341
00:19:38.678 --> 00:19:43.641
Doesn't anybody hate
anybody anymore?

342
00:19:43.683 --> 00:19:48.145
Hey. birds. don't snakes
always eat your eggs?

343
00:19:48.187 --> 00:19:49.689
Don't... Don't fall for that.

344
00:19:49.772 --> 00:19:53.109
Come on.
Someone's gotta have a grudge.

345
00:19:53.150 --> 00:19:55.111
This is too reformed!

346
00:19:55.152 --> 00:19:57.405
Oh. did we evolve too much?

347
00:19:57.446 --> 00:20:01.742
I-I actually have
deep respect for spacefarers.

348
00:20:01.826 --> 00:20:04.787
Parked your ships all nice
and neat up there.

349
00:20:06.831 --> 00:20:08.749
If it makes you feel any better.

350
00:20:08.791 --> 00:20:11.502
I didn't steal anything
from the glove boxes!

351
00:20:11.585 --> 00:20:17.967
No! I'm dying! Plants rule...

352
00:20:23.681 --> 00:20:25.850
So... that... that's it. then?

353
00:20:25.933 --> 00:20:29.729
I kinda thought we'd be returned
to our original bodies.

354
00:20:29.812 --> 00:20:32.690
No. no. no. no. we will.
We all just gotta believe.

355
00:20:32.732 --> 00:20:35.276
Yeah. we all just gotta
close our eyes.

356
00:20:35.359 --> 00:20:39.238
Mm. okay.
You guys got us this far.

357
00:20:47.413 --> 00:20:49.206
I don't feel anything.
Is it happening?

358
00:20:49.248 --> 00:20:50.875
Oh. it totally is.

359
00:20:50.916 --> 00:20:53.335
Ya gotta... Ya gotta
keep those eyes tight. though.

360
00:20:53.377 --> 00:20:54.795
You sound farther away.

361
00:20:54.837 --> 00:20:57.381
Ohh! My leaf became a hand!
It's working!

362
00:20:57.465 --> 00:20:59.175
Hope that happens to me.

363
00:20:59.216 --> 00:21:01.385
Whoa! Yeah! Ohhhh.

364
00:21:01.469 --> 00:21:05.389
Oh. ho. oh. it's so magical.

365
00:21:06.849 --> 00:21:10.227
Interesting how it happened
to them first.

366
00:21:10.269 --> 00:21:13.063
-Yeah!
-Hoo. hoo. hoo!

367
00:21:17.485 --> 00:21:19.445
Where have you two been all day?

368
00:21:19.528 --> 00:21:21.739
Nunya. What's that? Biology?

369
00:21:21.822 --> 00:21:24.909
I think I know a thing
or two about that.

370
00:21:27.328 --> 00:21:28.245
Nope.

371
00:22:02.780 --> 00:22:05.407
Op! Excuse us. Huh.

372
00:22:05.449 --> 00:22:07.618
Dude. That was totally Hyena #3.

373
00:22:07.660 --> 00:22:09.328
Guess people got out. huh?

374
00:22:09.411 --> 00:22:11.831
That is not
how I pictured him looking.

375
00:22:11.914 --> 00:22:13.374
Thanks. hon.

376
00:22:13.457 --> 00:22:16.585
This might sound crazy. but do
you know who I think I just saw?

377
00:22:16.627 --> 00:22:18.629
Was it the old man and boy
who saved us from prison

378
00:22:18.712 --> 00:22:20.923
but also left us trapped
in our animal bodies?

379
00:22:20.965 --> 00:22:22.967
You always fucking
step on my stories.

379
00:22:23.305 --> 00:23:23.407
